{% extends "layout/default.njk" %}
{% from "partials/quick_search/macro.njk" import quickSearch %}
{% from "govuk/components/button/macro.njk" import govukButton %}
{% block content %}
  <header class="full-width-banner" role="banner">
    <div class="banner-container">
      <img alt="Department for Environment Food &amp; Rural Affairs Logo" src="{{ assetPath }}/images/NCEA-logo-landscape.png" class="banner-container__ncea-logo">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl banner-container__heading-xl">Find natural capital data</h1>
        <span class="govuk-caption-l banner-container__caption-l">Use this service to search for data and information about the
          environment and ecosystems in the UK.</span>
        <span class="govuk-caption-l banner-container__caption-l">This service supports the use of natural capital approaches to
          gathering evidence and making decisions.</span>
      </div>
    </header>
    {{ quickSearch({
    searchPath: routes.searchResults,
    formId: quickSearchFID,
    isResultPage: false,
    searchInputError : searchInputError
  }) }}
    <div class=" govuk-grid-column-full  govuk-grid-row ">
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m educational-copy-container__heading-m">
        Natural capital
      </h2>
      <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        Natural capital is the parts of our natural environment that hold value for people, giving environmental, economic,
        societal and cultural benefits. It is nature’s stock of living and non-living resources – including ecosystems, species,
        freshwater, land, soils, minerals, air, and ocean – that provide flows of environmental (ecosystem) services.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full  govuk-grid-row">
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        Category search
      </h2>
      <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        All natural capital resources in this service are classified into broad themes and specific categories for better
        clarity and understanding.
      </p>
      {# disabling it enable once glossary link is available #}
      {# <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" class='help-link'>Natural capital classification glossary</a>
      </p> #}
      <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        Use these natural capital theme and classification filters to help narrow down your search
      </p>
    </div>
    {{ govukButton({
    id: 'guided-search',
    name: 'guided-search',
    text: "Start",
    isStartButton: true,
    href: routes.guidedSearch+'?level=1',
    attributes: {
      'data-do-quick-search': false
    }
  }) }}
    <article class="govuk-grid-row" role="article">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-full educational-copy-container">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-\!-static-margin-0 educational-copy-container__heading-m">Data types and sources</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">Use this service to find and access records and services such as:</p>
        <ul class='govuk-!-margin-bottom-6'>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">raw data</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">reports</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">maps</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">time-series data</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">annual publications</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">web mapping</li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">data viewer dashboards</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
          Marine and terrestrial data for the United Kingdom, UK Overseas Territories and other international locations are drawn
          from several sources, including:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">
            <a href="https://medin.org.uk/" target="_blank" class='govuk-link'>Marine Environmental Data & Information Network (MEDIN)</a>
          </li>
          <li class="govuk-body-m ncea-static-page-line-item">
            <a href="https://jncc.gov.uk/" target="_blank" class='govuk-link'>Joint Nature Conservation Committee (JNCC)</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-\!-static-margin-0 educational-copy-container__heading-m">NCEA programme</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">The Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs’(Defra’s)
          <a class='govuk-link' href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/natural-capital-and-ecosystem-assessment-programme" target="_blank">
          Natural Capital and Ecosystem Assessment (NCEA)</a>
          programme is delivering a nationwide survey of England’s land, coast, and sea: mapping the location, extent and
          condition of our ecosystems and the benefits they provide.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-4">Through comprehensive monitoring, innovative measurement and the development of tools and
          guidance, NCEA is providing insights on how and why our environment is changing and the impact of this – so that we can
          make informed decisions to better protect and manage our natural capital for people and the planet.
        </p>
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-\!-static-margin-0 govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">NCEA’s natural capital
          approach</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">Taking a natural capital approach is about incorporating the wider benefits of the environment
          into policy and decision making.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body ">Natural capital evidence and approaches help us to account for and articulate the different ways
          our natural assets hold value for people (be that cultural, social, economic or environmental value) and provide a
          framework for incorporating this into decision making. This reduces the risk of undervaluing our natural environment and
          helps to inform how we can better manage, protect, and enhance our natural assets and the services they provide.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  {% endblock %}
